Name Cavern, Passage
DARKNESS
DEEPCAVE
REGION 15
CALL 33
MINEB
*DESCRIPTION_START
This passage slopes downward from the northwest to the wall at the southeast corner. Some kind of dark stone along the walls and ceiling have been worn smooth. Along the backwall you see a crevice leading downward that has been ripped through the floor.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 63
EXIT NW 1214
IFVERB JUMP -1
	ECHO OTHERS %N jumps into the chaos towards oblivion.
	ECHO PLAYER You jump right into the crevice and realize your folly after it's too late.
	DAMAGEPLR CRUSH 150 You feel your body slam very hard into the ground.
	DAMAGEPLR SLASH 30 Your body is slashed from the sharp rocks at the bottom of the crevice.
	MOVE 1224
	POSITION LAY
ENDIF
IFVERB CLIMB 0
	CLEARVERB
	IFVAR SKILL5 < 1
	  ECHO PLAYER Having no skill in climbing whatsoever, you decide that leading such a climb would be folly.
	ELSE
	  EQUAL ROUNDTIME 10
	  SKILLCHECK 5 -30 DUMMY1
	  IFVAR DUMMY1 >= 0
	    ECHO GROUP You carefully make your way down into the crevice.
	    ECHO OTHGROUP %P makes the careful trek down into the crevice.
	    MOVEGROUP 1232
	    AFFECT 1232
	    ECHO OTHGROUP %P arrives after climbing carefully down the walls of the crevice
	  ENDIF
	  IFVAR DUMMY1 < -75
	    ECHO PLAYER You start the treacherous climb, but your footholds begin to crumble!
	      IFVAR SKILL5 < 5
		ECHO PLAYER You slip and fall into the chasm, hurtling through cold air you finally land on the ground.
		DAMAGEPLR CRUSH 150 You feel your body slam very hard into the ground.
		DAMAGEPLR SLASH 30 Your body is slashed from the sharp rocks at the bottom of the crevice.
		ECHO OTHERS You watch as %n, begins to make their way down the crevice, but gasp in horror as %s looses %i footing and tumbles from your vision! You are glad you weren't following.
		MOVE 1224
		POSITION LAY
	      ELSE
		ECHO PLAYER You retreat swiftly, realizing that it was only your calm and skill that saved you from certain doom.
		ECHO OTHERS %P begins making their way down the crevice, but the footholds begin to give way! Thinking quickly as only a master climber can, %n tracks a new route back to the top of the crevice.
	      ENDIF
	      ELSE
		IFVAR DUMMY1 < -40
	          ECHO PLAYER You make your way down the crevice, but your footing becomes unsteady! A rock becomes dislodged, tumbling its way into the chasm. You hastily retreat, breathing a sigh of relief that you survived.
		  ECHO OTHERS %P makes their way down the crevice, but %n becomes unsure of %i footing and is forced to retreat to the bottom of the ledge.
		ELSE
		  ECHO PLAYER You make your way down the crevice, but fail to find any further footholds or handholds. Alas, you are forced to backtrack to your starting point.
		  ECHO OTHERS %P makes their way down the crevice, but fails to find any further footholds or handholds. Alas, %s is forced to backtract to the beginning.
		ENDIF
	   ENDIF
         ENDIF
ENDIF

